15:
My feet sink into the ground here...
The heat is also oppressive...
19:
It's so different from a beach. There's
sand as far as the eye can see.
23:
Y-you're not planning on doing
anything crazy, right?
28: I'm not. I'll be right back.
33:
Incredible... I've never seen
machines like that before. Is the
entire floor made of metal?
39:
Whoa?! Was that one of those
organic life-forms folks have been
talking about?
41:
Haha, very funny. There's no way an
organic life-form could've moved
that fast.
44:
No matter how many times I see her
go, it's always impressive...
49:
Welcome back. Did you run into any
problems? This world should be
relatively safe, but I thought I should
check.
54:
Everything went well. I enjoyed
myself a lot.
57:
As for where we go next... Do you
know anywhere with a lot of snow I
could run through?
79:
Back already? Good timing. The
food is ready.
83:
We've got carrot soup today! It
should warm you right up.
88:
Thank you very much for cooking. I'd
love to have a bowl.
95:
Isn't it? It's got Special Week's seal of
approval.
100:
She ate so much that her stomach
looked like a balloon.
104:
...Is that why she went on a diet the
other day?
108:
Thank you, everyone. I appreciate
you taking me to all these locations.
113:
It was our pleasure. Besides, we
didn't have to go far.
118:
Yeah, don't mention it. It was a fun
little journey for us too.
122:
Why... did you go so far out of the
way for me?
125: None of you are my trainers...
130: Because we wanted to. We like you.
134:
I believe Special Week once said
that watching you run lifts one's
spirits.
137:
You could say we've come to
understand what she was talking
about.
143:
Spe said something like that... She
really knows how to make me blush...
147:
To be honest, Spe's the one who's
always lifting my spirits.
156:
Yes. She's always so cheerful and
looking out for me... I owe her more
than I can ever repay.
159:
You see, I have a habit of getting
stuck in my own head, and Spe
managed to pull me out of a
particularly bad episode.
162:
If she hadn't, I wouldn't have been
able to race... and see the scenery
that day...
170:
Yes. It was a big G1 race, and I had
to compete with a friend.
173:
I could feel her passion radiating
from next to me... The view from the
lead that day was spectacular.
176:
Before, I was satisfied just pulling
ahead to enjoy the peaceful
scenery, away from the chaos... but I
realized there's more to racing than
that.
179:
Hehe... I guess I love racing just as
much as she does.
184:
There is something to be said for
someone who can not only support
you, but also stand by you.
188:
Thank you for the meal. I'm plenty
warmed up now. I think... I'll go for
another run.
191:
Speaking about racing has me
feeling restless. Is it... okay for me to
go out again?
195:
We're already here. What reason
would we have to refuse?
199:
Should I keep the pot warmed up for
seconds?
212:
Phew... Running through the snow is
pretty nice.
215:
It all started like this... Alone, in the
quiet, with nothing else around.
220:
Some things haven't changed, but
others have.
223:
No matter what, the view from the
lead is mine.
227:
I won't hand it over to anyone. Not
Air Groove... Or Spe.
